helpdesk-note.body:
Hi farrells, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9632
The steps to install the box sync application on your laptop are included below. I will be marking this incident resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any additional feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated.
1) Navigate to 2) Login with your MSOE credentials 3) Select Continue 4) On the top right of the page you will see your name, click it and it should bring up a drop down menu 5) From this menu, select "Get Box Sync" 6) On the new page select "Get Box Sync For Windows" 7) This should start a download. Once this finishes, if you click on the file it will start the installation.
Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi farrells,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9632

The steps to install the box sync application on your laptop are included below. I will be marking this incident resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any additional feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated.

1) Navigate to
2) Login with your MSOE credentials
3) Select Continue
4) On the top right of the page you will see your name, click it and it should bring up a drop down menu
5) From this menu, select "Get Box Sync"
6) On the new page select "Get Box Sync For Windows"
7) This should start a download. Once this finishes, if you click on the file it will start the installation.


Thanks,
Thomas Schleich
helpdesk@msoe.edu
414-277-7288

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jason,

helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
User called in requesting a router for housing office at RWJ.
User says The internet reaches the office partially but not as good as it should be hence requesting a spare router if we have any would help

helpdesk-note.body:
Can you find out what this user is specifically requesting? There are only seven routers on campus, one for each network core. They are typically between $20,000 and $50,000. I don't think that's that this guy is looking for. We do not provide switches, hubs, routers, or APs to individuals, nor do we support or allow privately owned commercial routers (Dlink, Netgear, etc) on campus. We're less strict in the residence halls of MLH, RWJ, and Regents as they don't have MSOE provided wireless.
Please verify the problem the user is encountering and determine how best we can assist.
Thanks!

helpdesk-ticket.subject: 3rd tier Jenzabar SQL Server
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I’m working on an import from Jenzabar to CSGold. All is working well with one exception. When I run this SQL, the fields show fine with the ‘T’ noted in Select. When I do the import, the ‘T’ shows as a ‘1’. Any idea why that would happen? The ‘R’ and ‘C’ that I’m doing in the other two parts of the SQL work just fine, plus all the other fields are importing correctly. Just the ‘T’ is wrong. The results from the SQL show a ‘T’ in that location for import. Any ideas would be appreciated.
SELECT 'C|'+(RIGHT('000000000'+CONVERT(VARCHAR,degree_history.id_num),9)) + '|1|'+ degree_history.major_1 +'|'+ name_master.email_address +'|'+ biograph_master.udef_2a_1 +'|T|'+ student_master.current_class_cde FROM degree_history, name_master, student_term_sum, biograph_master, student_master WHERE ( name_master.id_num = degree_history.id_num ) and ( name_master.id_num = student_term_sum.id_num ) and ( student_term_sum.id_num = biograph_master.id_num ) and ( biograph_master.id_num = student_master.id_num ) and ( ( biograph_master.udef_2a_1 in ( 'UT', 'UF' ) ) AND ( student_term_sum.pt_ft_hours > 0 ) AND ( student_term_sum.yr_cde = '2017' ) AND ( student_term_sum.trm_cde = 'Q1' ) AND ( degree_history.cur_degree = 'Y' ) AND ( degree_history.major_1 not like 'PSEO' ) ) and (student_term_sum.udef_1a_1 is null and biograph_master.udef_2a_1 = 'UT')
Thanks☺
Sheila Barber Campus Card Administrator Milwaukee School of Engineering 1025 N Broadway CC435 Milwaukee WI 53202 Work: (414) 277-7460
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I’m working on an import from Jenzabar to CSGold.  All is working well with one exception.  When I run this SQL, the fields show fine with the ‘T’ noted in Select.  When I do the import, the ‘T’ shows as a ‘1’.  Any idea why that would happen?  The ‘R’ and ‘C’ that I’m doing in the other two parts of the SQL work just fine, plus all the other fields are importing correctly.  Just the ‘T’ is wrong.  The results from the SQL show a ‘T’ in that location for import.  Any ideas would be appreciated.
 
SELECT 'C|'+(RIGHT('000000000'+CONVERT(VARCHAR,degree_history.id_num),9)) + '|1|'+
      degree_history.major_1 +'|'+ name_master.email_address +'|'+ biograph_master.udef_2a_1 +'|T|'+ student_master.current_class_cde
    FROM degree_history,  
         name_master,  
         student_term_sum,  
         biograph_master,  
         student_master 
   WHERE ( name_master.id_num = degree_history.id_num ) and 
         ( name_master.id_num = student_term_sum.id_num ) and 
         ( student_term_sum.id_num = biograph_master.id_num ) and 
         ( biograph_master.id_num = student_master.id_num ) and 
         ( ( biograph_master.udef_2a_1 in (  'UT', 'UF' ) ) AND 
         ( student_term_sum.pt_ft_hours > 0 ) AND 
         ( student_term_sum.yr_cde = '2017' ) AND 
         ( student_term_sum.trm_cde = 'Q1' ) AND 
         ( degree_history.cur_degree = 'Y' ) AND 
         ( degree_history.major_1 not like 'PSEO' ) )
               and (student_term_sum.udef_1a_1 is null and biograph_master.udef_2a_1 = 'UT')
 
ThanksJ
 
Sheila Barber
Campus Card Administrator
Milwaukee School of Engineering
1025 N Broadway CC435
Milwaukee WI  53202
Work:  (414) 277-7460

Many thanks for all your help,
Prabhakar

Related question from me - Is this still the site a graduating student would go to switch from their old msoe.edu email to the new alumni.msoe.edu email? https://gapps.msoe.edu/alumni/index.php.   If there's a different process please let me know.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Kent Peterson, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9723
The link provided is the correct link for setting up an alumni email address. In regards to your question on forwarding, the mailbox is not deleted when the user's account is deactivated, the user simply loses accss. At some point, the mailbox will be deleted, however, until then the forwarding rule will continue to work. I will be marking this incident as resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns.
Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

I’d like to push everyone to using the online form, rather than paper. However, I don’t want to burden the staff in having to update attributes if it can be easily done with a script.
Thoughts?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Stacey,
Ann was able to make the following changes to the online RESPO form: 1. These are now processed nightly with a job- no more Process Internet Submissions for Julie :) 2. The submissions are connected to a new action in Notepad called RESPO- We are able to keep track of the date submitted (Item Date), agreement language (Item Description), and academic year (udef_10a_1 labled as RESPO YEAR).

helpdesk-note.body:
The report pulls in rows for distinct id nums with 403, 40a, 40b, 40s, or 40t rows from msc_chk_hist_itm_dtl_id_yr_v. There are two other nested reports in this report and those are pulling people with 403e rows. Normally any ids with a 403e row will also have a 403, 40a, 40b, 40s, or 40t row so the report has been working and adding up figures nicely the past few years. In this batch there happens to be one id num that only has a 403e row so they are not showing up in the base report. The problem is that their amount is still being added in the nested report totals since the nested reports are adding up all the values from any 403e rows.
I am going to recommend that they add 403e to their select statement in the basic report. I tested this and it seems like what they want.
Becky is going to give me a call when she's back in the office so I can go over the problem and how we can fix it.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
The report pulls in rows for distinct id nums with 403, 40a, 40b, 40s, or 40t rows from msc_chk_hist_itm_dtl_id_yr_v. There are two other nested reports in this report and those are pulling people with 403e rows. Normally any ids with a 403e row will also have a 403, 40a, 40b, 40s, or 40t row so the report has been working and adding up figures nicely the past few years. In this batch there happens to be one id num that only has a 403e row so they are not showing up in the base report. The problem is that their amount is still being added in the nested report totals since the nested reports are adding up all the values from any 403e rows.

I am going to recommend that they add 403e to their select statement in the basic report. I tested this and it seems like what they want. 

Becky is going to give me a call when she's back in the office so I can go over the problem and how we can fix it.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Katherine Vernezze, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9750
Below are the steps to install Follow You Printing. I will be marking this as resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns.
1) Press the Start Button in the bottom left hand of the screen 2) Search for and Select Run 3) In the box that appears type \\printers.msoe.edu 4) If prompted, enter your MSOE credentials 5) In the window that appears, Double click the printer labeled "Follow You Printing"
Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Katherine Vernezze,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9750

Below are the steps to install Follow You Printing. I will be marking this as resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. 

1) Press the Start Button in the bottom left hand of the screen
2) Search for and Select Run
3) In the box that appears type \\printers.msoe.edu
4) If prompted, enter your MSOE credentials
5) In the window that appears, Double click the printer labeled "Follow You Printing"

Thanks,
Thomas Schleich

Hello Nick and Joe
I hope that everything is going better with the interim president. I know from Joe that it hasn’t been the best year but I´m hoping it all works for the best.
I´m writing to both of you since you are my best contact from great people that I meet in MSOE and keep very good memories from both.
I´m still in contact with Joe a lot but I know that Nick could also give me some great advise and could aid PICO and myself to organize something for the foreign graduates and create like a networking for us.
I encounter a former alumni here in Mexico city out of 20 million and 5 years after I graduate. We found each other. He actually graduate in 1975. Hernando Cortina “Pico”.
I actually never thought of finding another graduate besides my brother here in Mexico city, everyone is afraid of the slightly mild cold weather of Milwaukee, even though it has some great places and I do have extremely awesome memory’s at my stay at MSOE and I try to other golfers go there I haven´t been successful.
What are your thoughts and what would be the path to do something here, Pico was think of getting the names of graduates and possibilities of contact them?
I´m adding two of my good friends that are foreign graduates, they started the ISA long time ago (International Student association) and I´m pretty sure they would have some valuable input on how to do a graduate international association and do some networking around the world.
Greetings,
Erik Macias

Pico,
Wow, I wish I could remember more foreign students. There were many from India. I do keep in contact with one, but he is a 21st century grad, and we're pretty old school. I do remember Juan and JosebPenaliza from Peru, a student from Aruba, one from Thailand, and several from Kuwait. I also remember an Iranian, whose last name was Tofighi, also one from Eithiopia. Ah the memory keeps clucking in, also three from France. And now that MSOE HAS a well-established exchange program with Lubeck, Germany. I know several of those students.
What I will do is contact Development and see if they can send me a list of foreign alums. I'll be in touch and let you know what happens.
Best, R Sent using OWA for iPad

I am confident with a little effort we can get this project “of the ground”, and it will be lots ‘of fun doing it.
By the way, My skype id is : hercor2, and phone numbers 5255 5652-2856(land line) , mobile: 0445532613896
Best regards,
Hernando (Pico)
De: Frankowski, Roger J. [mailto:frankows@msoe.edu] Enviado el: viernes, 12 de febrero de 2016 09:30 p. m. Para: HERNANDO CORTINA Asunto: Re: HERNANDO CORTINA
Hernando,
What a neat idea! I've been trying to formulate a group of MSOE retired faculty and staff. It's had its challenges, but some headway has been made. Besides you and Khalil, I maintain sporadic contact with an alum in Venezuela and one in India. It would be a wonderful networking tool.
Hope all is well with you and your family.
From the climatically more friendly region of Florida,
Rog
P.S. MSOE anxiously and nervously awaits the naming of a new president, having operated this year with an interim one.
Sent using OWA for iPad

My best regards,
Hernando Cortina

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Walk-Up Laptops in the Library
helpdesk-ticket.description: Hi Support, On Thursday, July 14, Tier 2 personnel came into the library to replace the walk-up laptops with newer laptops. The two student-workers were not able to finish the work, mainly because of problems with the locks. The student-workers deposited the six newer replacement laptops in my office for safekeeping when they left, and they indicated that they would return the next day (Friday July 15) to finish the job. They did not return the next day, so in the following week, I called the IT Helpdesk to get a status update. Thomas at the IT Helpdesk informed me that one of the student-workers had been ill on Friday July 15, and as a result, the student-workers were not able to return to the library on that day. Thomas indicated that he would get a status update to me. He subsequently left me a voicemail indicating that the student-workers would not be able to complete the job until the library purchased new locks for the laptops, and that IT personnel would contact me with details. I still have not yet been contacted about the situation. In the summer, the situation is not pressing, because we do not have large numbers of students using the library, but we are nonetheless being asked by students here and there about the status of our laptops. When someone has a chance, could they please contact me about this situation? We would would be happy to purchase locks, but I'm not sure which locks are preferred by IT. Thanks very much, Gary Shimek Director of the Library
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hi Support,

On Thursday, July 14, Tier 2 personnel came into the library to replace the walk-up laptops with newer laptops.  The two student-workers were not able to finish the work, mainly because of problems with the locks.  The student-workers deposited the six newer replacement laptops in my office for safekeeping when they left, and they indicated that they would return the next day (Friday July 15) to finish the job.  They did not return the next day, so in the following week, I called the IT Helpdesk to get a status update.  Thomas at the IT Helpdesk informed me that one of the student-workers had been ill on Friday July 15, and as a result, the student-workers were not able to return to the library on that day.  Thomas indicated that he would get a status update to me.  He subsequently left me a voicemail indicating that the student-workers would not be able to complete the job until the library purchased new locks for the laptops, and that IT personnel would contact me with details.  I still have not yet been contacted about the situation.  In the summer, the situation is not pressing, because we do not have large numbers of students using the library, but we are nonetheless being asked by students here and there about the status of our laptops.  When someone has a chance, could they please contact me about this situation?  We would would be happy to purchase locks, but I'm not sure which locks are preferred by IT. 

Thanks very much,

Gary Shimek
Director of the Library

helpdesk-note.body: Cameron, One more thing. We just took a look at the tables where you will place the six newer laptops. Previously on those tables, we had eight laptops, so we just noticed that you removed the network cables and power blocks for two laptops (because you're installing six laptops). Would you please re-install those power blocks and network cables? In the past, we've noticed that students often unplugged the locked-down laptops and plugged in their own laptops. If we retain network cables and power blocks for the seats that don't have locked-down laptops, this seating can nonetheless serve as places for students to plug in their own laptops. Let me know if you have questions about this. Thanks! --Gary

helpdesk-ticket.subject: German EE Exchange Students Card Access
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Dear Sir or Madam,
I am one of five German EE Exchange Students still attending MSOE until the end of September 16.
Even though we are still registered for a class (EE-499G) and officially graduating in the Fall Quarter 16, our card access got disabled due to attending the spring 16 commencement ceremony (the typical procedure for the German EE students at MSOE every year).
As we still need access to the library and other MSOE Buildings for our class, can you please get our card access and computer accounts reinstated?
This concerns the following five students:
· Pascal Dettmann (dettmannp@msoe.edu<mailto:dettmannp@msoe.edu>)
· Joscha Hoeck (hockj@msoe.edu<mailto:hockj@msoe.edu>)
· Jan-Eric Heyn (heynj@msoe.edu<mailto:heynj@msoe.edu>)
· Hendrik Sass (sassh@msoe.edu<mailto:sassh@msoe.edu>)
· Alexander Schmitz (schmitza@msoe.edu<mailto:schmitza@msoe.edu>)
Please tell me if you have any further questions or contact our advisor Dr. Mossbrucker or chair Dr. Williams directly if you need to get this approved. For Joscha and me you also got the approved “Request for Extension to Disabling of Computer Account” signed by Dr. Williams about 10 days ago, but it looks like this wasn’t processed.
Thank you,
Pascal Dettmann

helpdesk-ticket.description: Alicia Domack has been having trouble with ADP and Java not getting along. She usually uses Firefox. Upon realizing that ADP was not finding Java in Firefox she initially tried uninstalling / reinstalling Firefox and tried downloading java in Firefox. This did not solve the issue. We then tried using IE. IE would not recognize that Java was installed and would not successfully install java when that was attempted. We then uninstalled all Java from her machine via Control Panel and then installed Java from the Java website, but this did not alleviate the problem in either browser. Alicia is free today (8/1) anytime before 11, and tomorrow (8/2) before 9:30 and between 11-noon.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hello Katherine Quinton, All MSOE students that are currently registered for classes have MSOE email addresses attached to their accounts. You do not need to create your own account. One is created for you automatically.
There is an email associated with your account already. It is quintonkr@msoe.edu. Your password that you use to log into my.msoe.edu and blackboard is the same password as your email password.
Have a great day!

Have a great day!

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Judy,
You should now have an extension on that phone and a voicemail box which will send voicemails from 2361 to your email.
You will have to dial 7155 and log into voicemail with your extension 2361 and your pin 124578 to get a new pin setup and setup a greeting.
After that most people generally just use their email to monitor their voicemail. As long as you delete the voicemails from your email box they will delete from your voicemail and you shouldn't have any issues with the box ever getting full.
Tony

Hello Nick and Joe
I hope that everything is going better with the interim president. I know from Joe that it hasn’t been the best year but I´m hoping it all works for the best.
I´m writing to both of you since you are my best contact from great people that I meet in MSOE and keep very good memories from both.
I´m still in contact with Joe a lot but I know that Nick could also give me some great advise and could aid PICO and myself to organize something for the foreign graduates and create like a networking for us.
I encounter a former alumni here in Mexico city out of 20 million and 5 years after I graduate. We found each other. He actually graduate in 1975. Hernando Cortina “Pico”.
I actually never thought of finding another graduate besides my brother here in Mexico city, everyone is afraid of the slightly mild cold weather of Milwaukee, even though it has some great places and I do have extremely awesome memory’s at my stay at MSOE and I try to other golfers go there I haven´t been successful.
What are your thoughts and what would be the path to do something here, Pico was think of getting the names of graduates and possibilities of contact them?
I´m adding two of my good friends that are foreign graduates, they started the ISA long time ago (International Student association) and I´m pretty sure they would have some valuable input on how to do a graduate international association and do some networking around the world.
Greetings,
Erik Macias

Pico,
Wow, I wish I could remember more foreign students. There were many from India. I do keep in contact with one, but he is a 21st century grad, and we're pretty old school. I do remember Juan and JosebPenaliza from Peru, a student from Aruba, one from Thailand, and several from Kuwait. I also remember an Iranian, whose last name was Tofighi, also one from Eithiopia. Ah the memory keeps clucking in, also three from France. And now that MSOE HAS a well-established exchange program with Lubeck, Germany. I know several of those students.

Rog

helpdesk-note.body:
Hello Erik,
Did you graduate in 2009? Generally there are only a few weeks after graduation where your MSOE email account will still be active. You can create an alumni account if you have not already done that.
If you have not yet created your alumni email account, you can create it here: https://gapps.msoe.edu//alumni/
If you have forgotten your password for your @alumni.msoe.edu address, you can reset it here: https://gapps.msoe.edu//alumni/password/index.php
Your @msoe.edu address is not active and unless there were strange circumstances it has not been active for a long time.
I'm not sure why there are several staff members CC'd on this, so I apologize if this is spamming your mailbox.
Have a great day!

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi monroe, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9877
Below I have attached instructions to install the new version of Jenzabar. It operates exactly the same as the previous version. Please try following the instructions and let us if this resolves your issue.
1) Click the Start button in the bottom left hand screen 2) Select Control Panel 3) In the window that appears, look for "Get Programs". If it does not appear, make sure that the view by option in the top right of the window is set to category. 4) A window should appear with a list of programs. Search for and double-click Jenzabar Cloud EX6.
After a few moments a new link will appear on your Desktop. This link will operate the exact same as the previous link. Does this resolve your issue? Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Help installing MSOE printer
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello!
I'm a student at MSOE. I have class on Wednesday at Rosenburg hall. Is it possible to install a printer to print from my computer when I'm here?
Thanks, Becky Owens
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello!

I'm a student at MSOE.  I have class on Wednesday at Rosenburg hall.  Is it possible to install a printer to print from my computer when I'm here?

Thanks,
Becky Owens

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Rebecca,
You most certainly can install printers for you to use in the Rosenburg hall. Connect to the wireless network MSOE
This might ask for your MSOE credentials. If so, in the Username field type "MSOE\owensr", and your current MSOE password in the Password field. If you have a laptop on the MSOE wireless network, simply follow these steps: hit the Windows key and then R at the same time. Then in the Open field, type "\\printers.msoe.edu" and hit enter. This might ask for your MSOE credentials. If so, in the Username field type "MSOE\owensr", and your current MSOE password in the Password field. In the list of printers that should populate, double click on "Follow You Printing" and let the driver install. Congratulations! You can now use most printers on campus. Simply select "Follow You Printing" when you print a document, and then scan your ID at any of the Follow You Printing printers located in most buildings on Campus. The one in Rosenburg is located near the entrance to the building.
Have a great day!
If you are using a Mac, please follow the instructions attached to this message.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hey Rebecca,

You most certainly can install printers for you to use in the Rosenburg hall. 
Connect to the wireless network MSOE

This might ask for your MSOE credentials. If so, in the Username field type "MSOE\owensr", and your current MSOE password in the Password field.
If you have a laptop on the MSOE wireless network, simply follow these steps:
hit the Windows key and then R at the same time. 
Then in the Open field, type "\\printers.msoe.edu" and hit enter.
This might ask for your MSOE credentials. If so, in the Username field type "MSOE\owensr", and your current MSOE password in the Password field.
In the list of printers that should populate, double click on "Follow You Printing" and let the driver install.
Congratulations! You can now use most printers on campus. Simply select "Follow You Printing" when you print a document, and then scan your ID at any of the Follow You Printing printers located in most buildings on Campus. The one in Rosenburg is located near the entrance to the building. 

Have a great day!

If you are using a Mac, please follow the instructions attached to this message.
